Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow Darkstalker</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>3/26/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:06:34 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Announcement</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hi all! Well, I wanted to take a minute to share some news with you. Many of you know that I started on-line gaming back in Everquest in a quild called the Forgotten Truth. During that time I was involved in a terrible car accident here in Fort Worth when a drunk driver slammed into my car on the driver's side. I was pretty bad off and almost died as a result of injuries sufferd in the crash. Some how, I managed to pull through ... but not without the prayers and support of my game family who called and wrote to wish me the best. Through it all, a young lady, Kimberly Levitte, a co-worker of mine, watched over me, took me into her home for 24 hour care, logged into Everquest as Syndra to report on my condition to all, helped me walk again and got me through physical therapy. Without her I would be dead or confined to a wheelchair. As it is I'm back to being the big old bruiser that I always was in real life. I'm even playing hockey again with no pain! Ok, back to the point of this letter. I've let this go on for to long. God sent me an angel that day and I have now managed to capture her forever, for today I was blessed when I asked her to be my wife and she accepted. We wanted to share the news with those that matter most to us ... our friends and family from Asheron's Call and Everquest. We will never forget you.<br>
<br>
Rick Lange: Crow Darkstalker of Dereth</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Dierdra</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>3/27/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>7:02:50 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Congrats!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">May you have many happy years together! I wish you two the very best. <br>
